title: Willung couple vanish after leaving Seymour in Land Rover Discovery Wagon
text:
Mystery continues to shroud the sudden disappearance of a couple who vanished while travelling home.

Guy Beasley, 70, and his wife Susan, 69, told family they were headed back to their home in Willung, in remote Victoria, on Monday.

They were last seen driving away from a property in Whiteheads Creek, near the town of Seymour, and intended to pass through Dinner Plain.

Guy Beasley, 70, and his wife Susan, 69, told family they were headed back to their Willung home, in remote Victoria, on Monday

Susan Beasley was last seen with her husband in the couple's white 2016 Land Rover Discovery Wagon

Family have described their sudden disappearance as out of character and hold concern for their welfare.

Police are now searching for the couple and their vehicle which is a white 2016 Land Rover Discovery Wagon with registration plates AJT 166.

Guy is described as being 175cm tall and of medium build, who was last seen wearing dark coloured clothing.

Susan is 165cm tall with a medium build and was last seen wearing a rust coloured t-shirt, skinny jeans and black zip-up jacket with a grey quilted collar.
